                        "description":  "CollimateHealth is a Munich-based medtech startup developing microbeam radiation therapy, a cancer treatment that delivers arrays of ultra-thin, micrometre-scale radiation beams to destroy tumours while sparing healthy tissue and activating an anti-tumour immune response. Spun out of nearly a decade of research at the Technical University of Munich, the company has miniaturised the beamline needed to generate microbeams down to roughly 10 square metres, an order of magnitude smaller than the stadium-scale synchrotrons traditionally required. It works with academic and clinical partners including TUM University Hospital and The Royal Marsden in London.",
